SHG C++ library
***************

The SHG C++ library is a set of functions and classes written in ISO
C++. The library is intended for solving statistical and econometric
problems.

The library contains, inter alia, the following components:

* vector and matrix classes,
* implementation of linear regression model,
* implementation of basic sample statistics,
* implementation of normal hidden Markov and semi-Markov models,
* implementation of Gaussian and Laplace mixture models,
* implementation of Wald-Wolfowitz runs test,
* implementation of BDS test for independence.

This directory contains the 0.81 release of the library.

The documentation is generated by Doxygen in HTML format in the
doc/html directory during installation.

See the file INSTALL for installation instructions.

See the file LICENSE for licensing information.
